   <div class="COPY">
    <p>
     SNO+ is a new kilo-tonne scale liquid scintillator detector that will study
a variety of topics in neutrino physics. The primary goal of the experiment is
the search for neutrinoless double beta decay of
     <sup>
      130
     </sup>
     Te. The
experiment is located approximately 2 km underground in VALE's Creighton mine
near Sudbury, Ontario, Canada.
    </p>
